# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────── photographs ──
#
# photo-masters/ holds the original photographs. They are deliberately NOT in
# this repository: the site loads them from Cloudinary, resolved at build time
# through src/cloudinaryAssets.js — which IS committed, so a fresh clone builds
# a complete site without a single one of these files present.
#
# Keep this folder on your own machine and back it up. It is the master copy,
# and the only thing `npm run images:upload` reads.
#
# It also sits outside public/ on purpose. Anything under public/ is copied
# into build/ verbatim whether the site references it or not, which would put
# all 16 MB straight back into every deploy.
/photo-masters

# src/Images holds only what the bundle imports directly. Photographs are on
# the CDN; anything that lands here by accident stays out of the repo.
src/Images/*.jpg
src/Images/*.jpeg
src/Images/*.png

# …except the logo mark, which the header and footer import. It MUST be
# committed: photo-masters/ is gitignored, so on a clean CI checkout there is
# nothing to regenerate it from and the build would fail on a missing import.
!src/Images/logo-mark.png
